In two cases of bacterial pneumonia occurring in adults which were due to Klebsiella pneumoniae germs. The evolution became chronic with extensive invasion of the pulmonary tissues and destruction of the parenchyma. There was also multiple resistance of the germs to antibiotics as evidenced by sensitivity tests. The severe pleural complications have determined serious difficulties in the performance of the treatment. Confronted with such a condition the only therapeutical attitude consisted in testing the known antibiotics with efficiency in Klebsiella infections.